WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.035
<i>My name is avery ryan.</i>

00:03.037 --> 00:05.571
<i>I was a victim of cyber crime.</i>

00:05.573 --> 00:08.240
<i>Like you, I posted</i>
<i>on social media,</i>

00:08.242 --> 00:11.076
<i>Checked my bank account</i>
<i>balance online,</i>

00:11.078 --> 00:13.078
<i>Even kept</i>
<i>the confidential files</i>

00:13.080 --> 00:15.314
<i>Of my psychological practice</i>
<i>on my computer.</i>

00:17.083 --> 00:20.019
<i>Then I was hacked,</i>
<i>and as a result,</i>

00:20.021 --> 00:22.154
<i>One of my patients</i>
<i>was murdered.</i>

00:22.156 --> 00:25.024
My investigation into her death
<i>led me to the fbi,</i>

00:25.026 --> 00:27.626
<i>Where I joined a team</i>
<i>of cyber experts</i>

00:27.628 --> 00:30.529
<i>To wage a war against</i>
<i>a new breed of criminal</i>

00:30.531 --> 00:33.565
<i>Hiding on the deep web...</i>

00:33.567 --> 00:36.635
<i>Infiltrating our daily lives</i>
<i>in ways we never imagined...</i>

00:38.338 --> 00:40.339
<i>...Faceless...</i>

00:40.341 --> 00:42.541
<i>Nameless...</i>

00:42.543 --> 00:44.343
<i>Lurking inside our devices,</i>

00:44.345 --> 00:46.812
<i>Just a keystroke away.</i>

00:59.793 --> 01:01.527
Hey, man.

01:01.529 --> 01:02.528
Turn your phone off.

01:02.530 --> 01:03.695
What?
Turn...

01:03.697 --> 01:05.531
Your phone off.
The screen's bright.

01:05.533 --> 01:08.067
What the hell are you talking
about? My phone's in my pocket.

01:08.069 --> 01:09.535
Oh, really? Then what's that

01:09.537 --> 01:10.803
Lit under your chair?
That's not my phone.

01:10.805 --> 01:12.071
Attendant:
Hey, guys, come on.

01:12.073 --> 01:14.139
Quiet, or you're
both out of here.

01:29.522 --> 01:30.589
Oh, my god.

01:40.533 --> 01:42.568
Move! Out of the way, move!

01:49.442 --> 01:52.644
Run, run, it's a bomb, get away!

01:52.646 --> 01:54.746
Back away, back away,
it's a bomb!

01:55.648 --> 01:57.149
Move!

01:57.151 --> 01:59.451
(car alarms wailing)

02:16.336 --> 02:17.636
Sifter:
So far, we believe

02:17.638 --> 02:20.339
It was a remote detonation
using a tablet.

02:20.341 --> 02:22.141
Call you when
I have more.

02:22.143 --> 02:24.643
Somebody's putting a little
extra time in the field, huh?

02:24.645 --> 02:26.545
Yeah, when a bomb
detonates in the capital,

02:26.547 --> 02:28.614
(phone dings)
it is all hands on deck.

02:28.616 --> 02:30.482
Yeah. I spoke to atf.
They're waking up

02:30.484 --> 02:31.783
Every local scumbag
that's ever

02:31.785 --> 02:33.585
Set off a bomb.
As of now,

02:33.587 --> 02:36.522
The medical examiner just
confirmed six dead, 30 injured.

02:36.524 --> 02:38.524
You could multiply
that number by ten

02:38.526 --> 02:41.393
If that kid had not gotten
that bomb out of that theater.

02:41.395 --> 02:44.830
Avery, I gotta brief the
white house in 30 minutes.

02:44.832 --> 02:46.732
I'm gonna have
to show my hand.

02:46.734 --> 02:49.434
I want to be
holding some face cards.

02:49.436 --> 02:50.736
Let me see what the boys have.

02:50.738 --> 02:53.172
(helicopter hovering)

02:53.174 --> 02:54.840
What have we got?

02:54.842 --> 02:56.708
Collected phones
from witnesses.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.844
We scanned videos
and photos of the bombing.

02:58.846 --> 03:00.546
Did you find
any possible targets?

03:00.548 --> 03:02.381
No, but we did see a pattern.
Almost every phone

03:02.383 --> 03:03.815
That we snagged received
two text messages.

03:03.817 --> 03:07.352
First a number
and then a word: "kaboom!"

03:07.354 --> 03:09.454
Did all these phones
have the same text?

03:09.456 --> 03:13.759
But the numbers on all
the phones are different.
Krumitz: Yeah, we arranged

03:13.761 --> 03:15.961
<i>Them from highest to lowest,</i>
<i>like a countdown.</i>

03:15.963 --> 03:17.696
Hey, guys,

03:17.698 --> 03:19.298
These phones are from
inside the theater

03:19.300 --> 03:24.536
But all the numbers
were under 100.
All right, if the low numbers

03:24.538 --> 03:27.472
Were in the theater and those
closest to the explosion

03:27.474 --> 03:28.740
Were the highest,

03:28.742 --> 03:30.275
Then the tablet was counting up.

03:30.277 --> 03:31.610
This is crowdsourcing.

03:31.612 --> 03:33.278
<i>Every time the tablet</i>

03:33.280 --> 03:35.514
<i>Connected to a phone,</i>
<i>the number ticked up.</i>

03:35.516 --> 03:38.483
Ryan: <i>So the target used cell</i>
<i>phones to detonate the bomb.</i>

03:41.554 --> 03:43.989
When did you arrive
at the theater, mrs. Carter?

03:43.991 --> 03:45.958
We were late getting here.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.893
My son was upset

03:47.895 --> 03:50.662
Because he was
missing the previews.

03:50.664 --> 03:52.631
When did you receive
the first text?

03:52.633 --> 03:56.335
<i>Sam ran ahead to buy</i>
<i>the tickets and I went back</i>

03:56.337 --> 03:58.437
<i>To the car to grab a sweater.</i>
<i>It's a bomb, get away!</i>

03:58.439 --> 04:00.639
Move! Get away! It's a bomb!
Carter:
<i>That's when I saw the 200.</i>

04:00.641 --> 04:02.474
And then you received
the "kaboom!" text.

04:02.476 --> 04:03.675
Yes.

04:03.677 --> 04:05.744
When the explosion happened...

04:05.746 --> 04:08.347
I was near the car.

04:08.349 --> 04:11.550
And sam was
much closer to the...

04:14.654 --> 04:17.623
And now he's dead.

04:17.625 --> 04:19.725
The officer
that I spoke with

04:19.727 --> 04:22.761
Said that the 200 was
the last text that was sent out.

04:22.763 --> 04:25.264
Back away, back away!
Carter: <i>Means my phone</i>
<i>set off that bomb.</i>

04:25.266 --> 04:27.733
(explosion)
<i>I have to live with that.</i>

04:29.869 --> 04:31.837
My phone killed
all those people.

04:34.741 --> 04:35.874
It killed my son.

04:36.876 --> 04:39.044
Mrs. Carter...

04:39.046 --> 04:41.346
No, this is not your fault.

04:42.915 --> 04:44.783
(sighs, sniffles)

04:45.918 --> 04:48.820
I still haven't told my husband.

04:48.822 --> 04:52.057
I have to call
my husband.

04:52.059 --> 04:54.926
Of course.

05:11.344 --> 05:13.011
Wait, I thought we were
reassembling the bomb.

05:13.013 --> 05:14.579
We are.
Before we reassemble

05:14.581 --> 05:16.315
We got to find
the bomb parts first,

05:16.317 --> 05:18.850
Which means we need to pick out
every piece of shrapnel

05:18.852 --> 05:20.919
From all the debris
collected at the scene.

05:27.593 --> 05:29.861
And you really think we're gonna
find the tablet's hard drive

05:29.863 --> 05:32.064
In all of this stuff?
No matter
how powerful the blast,

05:32.066 --> 05:33.865
Bombs don't disintegrate.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.534
Usually you recover
all the pieces.

05:35.536 --> 05:36.868
Yeah.
I'm hitting a wall

05:36.870 --> 05:38.837
With these victims' phones.

05:38.839 --> 05:40.405
Turns out our
target anticipated

05:40.407 --> 05:41.840
We'd figure out
the tablet was the one

05:41.842 --> 05:43.008
That sent the "kaboom!" texts,

05:43.010 --> 05:44.976
So he protected himself.

05:44.978 --> 05:46.111
I mean, usually the tablet

05:46.113 --> 05:47.746
Would leave digital dust
on each phone,

05:47.748 --> 05:50.916
<i>And follow it back</i>
<i>to the target.</i>

05:50.918 --> 05:52.417
But we can't.

05:52.419 --> 05:55.687
Because every "kaboom!" text

05:55.689 --> 05:58.590
Was bundled with malware
that wiped the pairing record.

05:58.592 --> 06:02.127
<i>It's like a footprint being</i>
<i>compromised at a crime scene.</i>

06:02.129 --> 06:03.895
The hard drive isn't here.

06:06.366 --> 06:07.866
Too bad we can't
go back in time

06:07.868 --> 06:11.770
Where all the teeny-tiny
pieces went.

06:11.772 --> 06:16.041
Krumitz... Send all the media
you have to the cave.

06:21.514 --> 06:24.583
(wry chuckle) this is cyber
division's big, secret weapon?

06:24.585 --> 06:26.852
Just sit back and watch, here.

06:26.854 --> 06:28.086
Cave, tablet control.

06:31.057 --> 06:32.991
All right, you ready?

06:32.993 --> 06:34.760
Yeah. Security footage,
crime scene photos

06:34.762 --> 06:36.161
And pictures from
the victims' phones

06:36.163 --> 06:37.662
Are locked and loaded.

06:37.664 --> 06:39.731
Have the computer
pull it all up.
Yup.

06:42.668 --> 06:45.737
Good. All right, run the
3-d stitch program.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.141
Wow.

06:49.143 --> 06:50.642
Okay.

06:50.644 --> 06:52.144
Add the bomb blast plume,

06:52.146 --> 06:54.413
Eliminating
human carnage.

06:57.483 --> 07:00.719
Guys, guys.

07:00.721 --> 07:02.487
Damn, that was real.

07:02.489 --> 07:04.089
Mundo:
Okay.

07:05.425 --> 07:07.559
Let's find this hard drive.

07:07.561 --> 07:08.627
Yeah.

07:14.634 --> 07:16.134
Right here.

07:16.136 --> 07:18.570
That's the
hard drive.

07:18.572 --> 07:19.571
Good.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.473
Let's see where it lands.

07:21.475 --> 07:22.507
Krumitz, advance
the explosion.

07:22.509 --> 07:25.677
Um... I can't.

07:25.679 --> 07:27.913
The photos and the video
that we compiled only take us up

07:27.915 --> 07:29.581
To the moment the bomb exploded.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.516
After that, it's just
bits and pieces of data.

07:31.518 --> 07:32.818
Okay, so we know the hard drive

07:32.820 --> 07:34.519
Was propelled
in this direction, right?

07:34.521 --> 07:35.620
Mm-hmm.
And we also know

07:35.622 --> 07:37.756
Eventually,
it would have to land.

07:37.758 --> 07:39.691
Means it's somewhere
further down the alley.

07:39.693 --> 07:41.159
Yeah, but we collected every
of bit shrapnel from the alley

07:41.161 --> 07:44.696
Then something interrupted
the course of its trajectory,

07:44.698 --> 07:47.499
So, krumitz, run a line from
the point of the bomb blast

07:47.501 --> 07:49.835
Through the hard drive
and advance the alley toward us.

07:49.837 --> 07:52.737
Okay, the flight path
of the hard drive takes us

07:52.739 --> 07:55.140
Right into these two people--
this is about where

07:55.142 --> 07:56.641
It would have landed,
right about there.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.009
Good work.

07:58.011 --> 08:00.078
Send me a still of the hard
drive's final position.

08:00.080 --> 08:02.681
I'm gonna find out
who those two vics are.

08:02.683 --> 08:04.082
Krummy...

08:04.084 --> 08:05.784
I was thinking
after we catch that bomber,

08:05.786 --> 08:07.686
Maybe me and you can
come back here

08:07.688 --> 08:08.954
And play that new
first-person shooter.

08:08.956 --> 08:12.824
I got first.
(chuckles)

08:12.826 --> 08:15.193
Hey...

08:15.195 --> 08:17.262
Krummy?

08:18.197 --> 08:19.631
Krummy!

08:21.234 --> 08:22.868
Coroner:
<i>I believe these</i>

08:22.870 --> 08:24.936
Are the two victims
you're looking for.

08:27.573 --> 08:30.976
Both suffered injuries
in the bomb blast.

08:38.651 --> 08:40.819
(grunts)

08:43.756 --> 08:45.824
There's the hard drive.

09:01.307 --> 09:03.642
Thank you.

09:03.644 --> 09:06.278
(sighs) I can't shake
this mrs. Carter story.

09:06.280 --> 09:08.613
Yeah, outliving your
kid is tragic enough,

09:08.615 --> 09:09.948
But thinking
you killed him?

09:09.950 --> 09:11.850
There's no words
for that.

09:11.852 --> 09:14.119
So... M.E.'s office called.

09:14.121 --> 09:16.721
They finally I.D.'d
the rest of the bodies.

09:16.723 --> 09:18.757
Now, two were
congressional staffers.

09:18.759 --> 09:21.593
I'm being asked if I think
they were targeted.

09:21.595 --> 09:23.595
There's no way our target
could've been certain

09:23.597 --> 09:25.263
Who would be near
the blast when it blew.

09:25.265 --> 09:28.066
They're just
wrong place, wrong time.

09:28.068 --> 09:30.168
How we coming on
that target profile?
I compiled

09:30.170 --> 09:33.672
A list of our target's tactic,
techniques, and procedures,

09:33.674 --> 09:35.707
Like using a wireless
device as a trigger.

09:35.709 --> 09:37.876
There are nine dossiers

09:37.878 --> 09:40.011
In the fbi
database that fit.

09:40.013 --> 09:41.212
Three are dead and one

09:41.214 --> 09:42.814
Is serving a
life sentence.

09:42.816 --> 09:44.816
Eyewitnesses said
that the bomb was made

09:44.818 --> 09:46.785
Out of a shoebox
and duct tape.

09:46.787 --> 09:49.087
So bombers are monogamous
with their materials.

09:49.089 --> 09:52.724
Older materials suggests
someone over 35.

09:52.726 --> 09:55.694
And then
there were two.
The one on the left

09:55.696 --> 09:58.296
Is currently under surveillance
in san antonio.

09:58.298 --> 10:00.599
The other's been off the grid
for over a year.

10:00.601 --> 10:02.734
That is our target.
No name, no photo.

10:02.736 --> 10:06.605
We know that he detonated a bomb
in Italy and another in France.

10:06.607 --> 10:08.073
And now, here in the states.

10:08.075 --> 10:10.241
Hey, you guys got to
check out this web site.

10:10.243 --> 10:13.211
It's trending like crazy
on togglefly, friendagenda--

10:13.213 --> 10:15.880
It is everywhere.

10:15.882 --> 10:18.049
Who's behind this?
We don't know.

10:18.051 --> 10:20.285
Metadata's been scrubbed.
It's a dead end.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.287
Scrambled voice: You are
responsible for this bombing.

10:22.289 --> 10:24.122
You could've prevented it

10:24.124 --> 10:25.624
If you'd just
left your cell phone at home.

10:25.626 --> 10:27.626
Your addiction to technology

10:27.628 --> 10:29.294
Is going to kill you.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.630
And now for another lesson.

10:31.632 --> 10:34.065
When this web site gets
one million viewers,

10:34.067 --> 10:36.234
A second bomb will explode.

10:36.236 --> 10:37.736
Ryan:
Our target

10:37.738 --> 10:39.638
Is using page views
on a web site

10:39.640 --> 10:41.006
To make the public responsible

10:41.008 --> 10:42.407
For the next explosion.

10:42.409 --> 10:45.010
The site was uploaded
a few hours ago.

10:45.012 --> 10:48.279
Has already 460,000 views
and counting.

10:48.281 --> 10:52.017
The video starts playing
the moment you access the site.

10:52.019 --> 10:53.418
We have to pull it down now.

10:53.420 --> 10:54.919
We've tried to hack it.

10:54.921 --> 10:56.721
The firewall is too robust.
We're working on it.

10:56.723 --> 10:57.789
Well, work faster.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.424
That url cannot remain online.

10:59.426 --> 11:01.326
Let's find out
where this site

11:01.328 --> 11:04.029
Is being physically hosted,
and have an fbi intrusion squad

11:04.031 --> 11:06.898
At the ready, in case
we got to hit a building

11:06.900 --> 11:08.400
And unplug a server here.

11:08.402 --> 11:10.235
Meantime, we've got
to alert the public

11:10.237 --> 11:15.173
No, no, no. Simon,
an alert will only
pique interest

11:15.175 --> 11:17.409
And drive people to
view the footage.

11:17.411 --> 11:18.943
Look how many views
we already have.

11:18.945 --> 11:21.413
This is mass
cyber voyeurism.

11:21.415 --> 11:23.982
They are visiting that site
because they don't understand

11:23.984 --> 11:26.217
This is not a joke,
and it's not a game.

11:26.219 --> 11:28.319
And every view brings us
one step closer

11:28.321 --> 11:30.422
To a blast site
and a body count.

11:30.424 --> 11:32.424
Clearly, our target

11:32.426 --> 11:34.693
Understands social
media addicts.

11:34.695 --> 11:37.128
People who are compelled
to go to the site, thinking,

11:37.130 --> 11:40.432
"if I'm viewer
500,000 or 600,000,

11:40.434 --> 11:43.435
"or 900,000, there
are no consequences.

11:43.437 --> 11:45.437
"all that matters is
the one millionth view,

11:45.439 --> 11:47.739
So why not see
what's trending?"

11:47.741 --> 11:51.242
Avery, I get
the psychology, I do,

11:51.244 --> 11:52.844
But we cannot just sit by

11:52.846 --> 11:54.979
And watch that counter
keep ticking up.

11:54.981 --> 11:56.981
By making that announcement,
we can stretch it...

11:56.983 --> 11:58.950
No, the announcement

11:58.952 --> 12:00.418
Will not just
alert the public.

12:00.420 --> 12:02.020
It will alert the target.

12:02.022 --> 12:05.857
And there could be very
real repercussions.

12:05.859 --> 12:07.492
What do you suggest?

12:07.494 --> 12:11.429
We need to find a way to break
through that site's firewall.

12:11.431 --> 12:13.431
Then, you better get
moving here, avery,

12:13.433 --> 12:16.167
'cause human curiosity puts us
on an unpredictable clock.

12:16.169 --> 12:18.269
We got no way
of knowing when or where

12:18.271 --> 12:19.771
That bomb is gonna explode.

